items.text: Yes, the Thai stall is really good!
Famous char kway teow and curry chicken rice stall are your best bets here.
My mommies shop!! Best gila!! #01-78.. Must try!!
Mas seafood is great, but don't catch them at peak hour as they get orders wrong & have bad service. The roast meat stall 2nd row from right, queenstown char kuay teow & ruyi vegeterian stall are :)
Yummy fishball
Uncle lee's Hong Kong noodle & rice has one of the best soy sauce chickens. Closed on wed and thurs.
Kway chap damn good 01-121
There is a very nice muffin shop along uncle lim shop..they sell very nice bread too..after lunch Time they close le and weekend they don't sell bread..ONLY Muffins!!!
Try Song Heng Fishball Noodle. It's worth the queue
Malay stall 01-78 power!!!
try the Ming Kitchen Seafood... cheap n decent
golden barn confectionary muffins are a must have!
The Thai food stall is not worth trying. Tried n was disappointed
Nan fang cooked food at #01-80 is 
The Mix rice along the thai food stall POWER LOR,very homecook dishes,the LONG Q is worth!
Song heng fish ball nice!!
Must try e konak western here!! All e food is nice n worth to buy...
Ban mian here is nice ! ^^
ABC Ah Hwa Fishball Noodles - Featured in Top 10 Fishball Noodles by Shin Min Daily. Try it!
Early morning,ABC fishball noodle is nice!
Uncle lim's pancake must have!! Red bean so yummy! Finish by 12pm
Any gado-gado there?
The fishball noodles here are awesome and crunchy
Try the Monkey Thai Food. Good and cheap
Fish soup. With rice.
HerWorldPlus recommends: Hai Kee Teochew Char Kway Teow #102, home-cooked curry rice fr Nan Fang Cooked Food #80, Sampan porridge & boneless fried chicken wings fr Fei Lou Porridge #116
Local kopi. After sampling fr a few stalls, my vote goes to Soon Huat #01-106 for smooth bitter kopi. Fragrant, w/o any of that musty coffee bag smell u get fr many others
Guan Seng Carrot Cake a must try. For chilli lovers the chilli used is hand made and spicy.
Try the pretty new stall of the Thai food
Must eat the Thai food. Cheap n nice
Try the 肥老 porridge which opens at 7pm and 松兴 fishball noodles which opens in the morning.
Must try the mee siam flavour bee hoon... #01-123
Song Heng noodle!!!
I tried the ABC fish ball noodle. The noodles are very smooth and cooked just nice. I would recommend this stall to fish ball noodle lovers
Mi chiam kueh (local pancake). Uncle Lim Traditional Pancake #01-120 has a recipe that leaves edges very crispy. Fillings options: ground peanut, grated coconut, tau sar (red bean paste) & cheese
Prata: We happily chewed into crispy roti pratas fr Al-Amin #01-95. Very 'q' (has bite) but their curry cd do w more taste
I still love 肥佬 and 松兴!
Try Chicken Wing rice at REJOICINGS... MY Favourite
Soy sauce chicken noodles: Locals patiently wait for their bowl fr Uncle Lee's #01-127. Succulent fragrant chicken cuts accompany 'q' noodles. Stall also sells WTM, beef brisket & stewed chicken feet
Thai store's food here is super delicious! :) Especially with a drink of fruit juice which is beside the Thai food store is one out of nice combination! :D.
yummy..yummy
U must try the Nan Fang cooked food....the curry is hot & delicious!
IRT lagi belanja mingguan :P
The lau pat sat kway chap here is very good. Excellent chilli sauce too...
Dai Ming Cooked Food #01-121 - Must Try..
The Economy Snacks are good👍 and tasty
Tried Nan Fang today.. Ya.. The food is nice.. Like the curry & the pop corn Chix.. Crunchy.. But was wondering where is the Ban Mian??? Anyone can tell me then I can go try it too..
Do not eat the fried dry beef horfun here. It's so salty!
The muffin stall in the market is delicious
Fei lou porridge is amazing !!! Must try
Find of d month. Tks to 4SQ friend Songhua, discovered genuine handmade fishball noodle stall. Fishballs was super bouncy & chewy, noodles 'q', & soup light & clean. Deserves spot as top 10 in SG
food stalls are good here
01-83 : Monkey Thai Seafood best ah!!!! Love the green curry, :)
i love porkribs rice here..love it
Fishball noodles: Hua Fa #01-97 serves a delicious bowl but uses a lot of oil. So let them know early...
Decent Kway Chap & braised duck wings.   I asked them to omit all pig's spare part.
Veg stall at #01-101 is good! :)
Best Prata@ Al-Amin Food Stall
Wantan noodles: Hong Fu #01-103 WTM has shrimps in their wantans. Rare. Charsiew was disappointing though for a stall that sells roasted meats. Noodle was not 'q'
Song heng fish noodle is very nice!
With Momo Around, Life's exciting n fun :D
Nan fang mee hoon w chilli, SEX
Uncle Lee's Hong Kong Noodle & Rice stall at 01-127 closes on Wednesday and Thursday. Good chicken rice or noodles.
Monkey Thai Seafood: Don't forget to order Fried Prawn Cake!
New porridge stall 香記粥品 no standard. Watery porridge with lumps of 'rice cake'. Pork meat is seasoned though.
Fei Lou boneless fried chicken wing is shiok!!open 6pm onwards!!!!!!!!
Claypot rice is great! Very tasty. Very good. Must try. Stall # 01-108 Yuan Wei
Dun try the desserts stall. Something wrong with the food. Unnatural chemical taste
Hai Kee Famous Kway Teow and Al-Amin Food Stall...check their awards at their store too...
The Economy Snacks are good and tasty👍
The food are nice
